description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Rotherham NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Registered Nurse Associate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 4&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flexible Arrangements – Full or Part Time / Internal Rotation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Division of Medicine&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Division of Medicine is looking for a passionate, hardworking and friendly individuals to join the Division in the role as a Registered Nurse Associate (Band 4), there are a number of opportunities in the following specialties across the division.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Respiratory Medicine&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cardiology Medicine&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Health Care for Older People&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stroke Care - Acute and Rehabilitation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Acute Medicine – Acute Medical Unit / Rapid Assessment&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Diabetes and Endocrinology / Gastroenterology &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is a really exciting time here at The Rotherham NHS Foundation Trust as we are&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Currently transforming the way in which we deliver healthcare in Rotherham, to align with our vision as an organisation of becoming an outstanding trust, delivering excellent healthcare at home, in our community and in our hospital, to deliver this model of health care we are looking to recruit Band 4 Registered Nurse Associates across the division who will join us in our aim to become an outstanding division, delivering safe, effective, well led, responsive care to our patients by individuals and teams that are well led, kind, caring and compassionate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role of the Nursing Associate is to work with the multi professional team and the Registered Nurse to assess, plan, organise and deliver clinical care in line with service and patient need working independently under the leadership of registered nurses, working within the sphere of nursing care and within all aspects of the nursing process&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We appreciate the demands of a work life balance and we are always looking at ways to deliver flexibility to our colleagues while delivering a service to our patients and community, therefore we offer a number of flexible working arrangements which can meet your individual situation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested to find out more about the exciting opportunities in the Division of Medicine we would love to hear from you, please feel free to make contact with senior nursing colleagues (as below) we can offer informal visits and conversations. We look forward to hearing from you;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please Contact;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mrs Clare Lunn, Matron for the Division of Medicine Clare.lunn@nhs.net 01709 428045&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mrs Gail Smith, Deputy Head of Nursing, Division of Medicine gail.smith22@nhs.net 01709 427786&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
